      "timestamp": "2026-05-17",
      "error_message": "COM5 boot loop: invalid header 0x22294745 after reflash",
      "file": "flashtool/firmware/gmabutton.bin",
      "root_cause": "gmabutton.bin is a raw app partition binary. Flashing it at 0x0 overwrites the bootloader with app data — device cannot boot. Additionally, passing merged binary + NVS config in a single esptool write_flash command errors with 'Detected overlap at address: 0x9000' because the merged binary already covers the NVS region.",
      "fix": "Two separate esptool commands: (1) idf.py merge-bin -o <absolute_path>/gmabutton_merged.bin, then flash merged at 0x0. (2) flash gmabutton1_config.bin at 0x9000 as a separate esptool call. Both verified with hash. Device restored.",
      "tags": [
        "flash",
        "bootloader",
        "merge-bin",
        "esptool",
        "nvs",
        "com5"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
